getTableAttributeHandler

public java.util.LinkedHashMap<java.lang.String,AttributeHandler> getTableAttributeHandler()
Returns the list which maps entry names formated in the standard of Saada (keys) to their objects modelling attribute informations (values). Generally the object modelling attribute informations is a AttributeHandler. This method contrary in the method getKW() does not model the list in memory. So that this one does not return null, it is beforehand necessary to have already created the list with the other method (getKW()). Cross_reference of the homonymous method defined in the current object product (and by relationship in the current product file).

Overrides:
getTableAttributeHandler in class Product
Returns:
Hashtable The list which maps attribute names to their informations.
